50.4.1.3 - Nonroutine Supplies (Reportable) 
(Rev. 10438, Issued: 11-06-20, Effective: 03-01-20, Implementation: 01- 11-21) 

Nonroutine supplies are identified by the following conditions: 
 1. The HHA follows a consistent charging practice for Medicare and other patients 
receiving the item; 

2. The item is directly identifiable to an individual patient; 

3. The cost of the item can be identified and accumulated in a separate cost center; 
